verbose_text: Although available samples were from obese individuals in which the ChREBP axis is expected to be strongly suppressed, a strong correlation was nonetheless observed between ACLY and both GLUT4 and ChREBPalpha (ChREBPbeta was undetectable in these samples; XREF_FIG and XREF_FIG), consistent with the notion that GLUT4, ACLY, and ChREBP expression are co-regulated in human adipose tissue.
